My bargain-priced room was small but perfectly clean and gleaming, modern design, well lighted, elegant furnishings with professional decor and a super-comfortable bed.	The wine tasting was lovely every evening, great location, very confortable beds/pillows, very clean, homey atmosphere, helpful staff/cleaners.	I love Kimpton hotels for their cleanliness, service, decor, and small/mid-size hotel feel.	I would classify this hotel as a bit old school in terms of the decor and furnishings, but very well maintained.	We like the Vintage Park because although you are in a large city, it has the feeling of being at a country inn with the inviting fireplace and comfy overstuffed furniture in the lobby.